人類食用蕈菇的歷史悠久。距今13000年的智利考古遺址即有發現食用蕈，更確切的證據在西元前數百年的中國。中國人同時用蕈類當作食物（香菇、木耳）和藥物（冬蟲夏草、灵芝）。[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]和[[古希臘|古希臘]]人也會食用蕈類，特別是上層階級；羅馬皇帝的食物會有專人先試吃確保安全。因為蕈菇很容易乾燥保存，因此在許多地方是冬季的重要存糧。<ref name=Boa2004/><ref name=Jordan2006>{{cite book |author=Jordan P. |title=Field Guide to Edible Mushrooms of Britain and Europe |year=2006 |publisher=New Holland Publishers |isbn=978-1-84537-419-8 |page=10 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=t1FBH5cNTe0C&pg=PA10 |access-date=2015-08-12 |archive-date=2016-06-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610142801/https://books.google.com/books?id=t1FBH5cNTe0C&pg=PA10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

相較於歐陸，英國文化特別排斥採野菇作為食物，並將此文化傳到北美、紐澳等殖民地。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tcpermaculture.com/site/2013/07/01/fighting-fungophobia-or-mycophobia-the-fear-of-mushrooms/|title=存档副本|access-date=2020-11-18|archive-date=2021-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411164544/https://tcpermaculture.com/site/2013/07/01/fighting-fungophobia-or-mycophobia-the-fear-of-mushrooms/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

許多傳統文化都會用[[迷幻蘑菇|迷幻蘑菇]]作為宗教和醫療用途。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.samorini.net/doc/sam/sah_int.htm |title=The oldest Representations of Hallucinogenic Mushrooms in the World. |publisher=[http://www.samorini.net/ www.samorini.net/] |accessdate=2007-04-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060116104741/http://www.samorini.net/doc/sam/sah_int.htm |archivedate=2006-01-16 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>John M. Allegro"[http://www.phreak.co.uk/debespace/John_Allegro___The_Sacred_Mushroom_And_The_Cross.pdf The Sacred Mushroom And The Cross] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100215041122/http://www.phreak.co.uk/debespace/John_Allegro___The_Sacred_Mushroom_And_The_Cross.pdf |date=2010-02-15 }}"</ref>

==食用==
{{further|食用蕈列表}}
[[File:MorelShroom.JPG|thumb]]]]
人類食用的蕈類中，只有一小部份有商業種植及銷售。商業化的種植對生態保育相當重要；有商業銷售但仍不易人工種植的物種很容易面臨滅絕的危機，如[[雞油菇|雞油菇]]在歐洲的情況。商業種植的食用蕈中較常見的有[[香菇|香菇]]、[[草菇|草菇]]、[[洋菇|洋菇]]、[[金針菇|金針菇]]、[[杏鮑菇|杏鮑菇]]、[[木耳|木耳]]等等。

===營養價值===
雖然說菇類不需要陽光就可以生長，但經照射陽光的洋菇會大幅提高其[[維生素D|維生素D]]含量。這是因為洋菇在照射紫外線時，能將[[麥角固醇|麥角固醇]]轉換為維生素D2，這和人類照射紫外光時合成維生素D3的過程類似<ref name="LATeat">{{cite news |author=Bowerman S |date=2008-03-31 |title=If mushrooms see the light |work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]] |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/mar/31/health/he-eat31 |accessdate=2015-08-12 |archive-date=2011-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110904135924/http://articles.latimes.com/2008/mar/31/health/he-eat31 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Koyyalamudi SR, Jeong SC, Song CH, Cho KY, Pang G |title=Vitamin D2 formation and bioavailability from Agaricus bisporus button mushrooms treated with ultraviolet irradiation |journal=J Agric Food Chem |volume=57 |issue=8 |pages=3351–5 |date=April 2009 |pmid=19281276 |doi=10.1021/jf803908q}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Lee GS, Byun HS, Yoon KH, Lee JS, Choi KC, Jeung EB |title=Dietary calcium and vitamin D2 supplementation with enhanced Lentinula edodes improves osteoporosis-like symptoms and induces duodenal and renal active calcium transport gene expression in mice |journal=Eur J Nutr |volume=48 |issue=2 |pages=75–83 |date=March 2009 |pmid=19093162 |doi=10.1007/s00394-008-0763-2}}</ref>。在採收前照一小時的紫外光能讓洋菇的維生素D含量達到一日建議攝取量的2倍，採收後照5分鐘則能達到4倍。<ref name="LATeat" /><ref>{{cite journal |author=Koyyalamudi SR, Jeong SC, Song CH, Cho KY, Pang G |year=2009 |title=Vitamin D2 formation and bioavailability from Agaricus bisporus button mushrooms treated with ultraviolet irradiation |journal=J Agric Food Chem |volume=57 |issue=8 |pages=3351–5 |publisher= |doi=10.1021/jf803908q |pmid=19281276 |pmc= |url= |accessdate=2013-03-17}}</ref>

===處理方式===
[[File:Dried_mushrooms.jpg|thumb]]
有些種類的蕈菇生食有毒或無法消化，但可以在煮熟後食用。一般野外採集的菇都建議煮熟後再食用，除了去除蕈菇本身可能帶有的毒素之外，也避免細菌或寄生蟲汙染。

很多食用蕈都可以乾燥保存，在使用時先泡水或直接水煮即可復原。用來泡蕈菇的水也可以用來入菜，但底下如果有土沙的部份要倒掉。

蕈菇的料理方式可以煮、炒、烤、炸、燙、醃漬等等，也以做成湯、醬汁、沙拉。<ref>{{cite web|title=Mushroom recipes|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/food/mushroom|publisher=BBC Food|access-date=2015-08-12|archive-date=2021-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516073045/https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/mushroom|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==藥用==
在民俗療法中，有些蕈類被認為具有藥用效果，最主要的例子是在亞洲地區，特別是中醫體系<ref name=Hobbs1995>{{cite book |author=Hobbs CJ. |title=Medicinal Mushrooms: An Exploration of Tradition, Healing & Culture |publisher=Culinary Arts Ltd |location=Portland, Oregon |year=1995 |page=20 |isbn=1-884360-01-7}}</ref>。許多蕈類仍未接受現代西方醫學的驗證，因此在其他地區（如美國）一般不能作為藥物出售<ref>{{cite journal |author=Sullivan R, Smith JE, Rowan NJ |year=2006 |title= Medicinal mushrooms and cancer therapy: translating a traditional practice into Western medicine|journal=Perspect Biol Med |volume=49 |issue=2 |pages=159–70 |publisher= |doi= 10.1353/pbm.2006.0034|pmid=16702701 |pmc= |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_perspectives-in-biology-and-medicine_spring-2006_49_2/page/159|accessdate=2013-03-17}}</ref>。

有些中醫常用的藥用蕈類正逐步接受現代醫學的研究，大多仍在細胞株、[[動物實驗|動物實驗]]和初階人體實驗的階段<ref name=Borchers>{{cite journal |last1=Borchers |first1=A. T. |last2=Krishnamurthy |first2=A. |last3=Keen |first3=C. L. |last4=Meyers |first4=F. J. |last5=Gershwin |first5=M. E. |title=The Immunobiology of Mushrooms |journal=Experimental Biology and Medicine |volume=233 |issue=3 |pages=259–76 |year=2008 |pmid=18296732 |doi=10.3181/0708-MR-227}}</ref>。目前的研究已顯示有些蕈類粹取物具有抗菌、消炎、抗病毒、止痛、抗癌、心血管及降血糖等效果。其中一些如[[多醣體K|多醣體K]]（polysaccharide K）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mskcc.org/mskcc/html/69194.cfm |title=Coriolus Versicolor |work=About Herbs, Botanicals & Other Products |publisher=Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center |access-date=2015-08-12 |archive-date=2011-11-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111102071932/http://www.mskcc.org/mskcc/html/69194.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[多醣肽|多醣肽]]（polysaccharide peptide）<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ng |first1=T. B. |title=A review of research on the protein-bound polysaccharide (polysaccharopeptide, PSP) from the mushroom Coriolus versicolor (basidiomycetes: Polyporaceae) |journal=General Pharmacology: the Vascular System |volume=30 |issue=1 |pages=1–4 |year=1998 |pmid=9457474 |doi=10.1016/S0306-3623(97)00076-1}}</ref>、[[香菇多糖|香菇多糖]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mskcc.org/mskcc/html/69279.cfm |title=存档副本 |access-date=2015-08-12 |archive-date=2012-12-28 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20121228025756/http://www.mskcc.org/mskcc/html/69279.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>等已經在一些亞洲國家投入醫療使用<ref name="CancerResearchUK">{{cite journal |last1=Sullivan |first1=Richard |last2=Smith |first2=John E. |last3=Rowan |first3=Neil J. |title=Medicinal Mushrooms and Cancer Therapy: translating a traditional practice into Western medicine |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_perspectives-in-biology-and-medicine_spring-2006_49_2/page/159 |journal=Perspectives in Biology and Medicine |volume=49 |issue=2 |pages=159–70 |year=2006 |pmid=16702701 |doi=10.1353/pbm.2006.0034}}</ref><ref name=Borchers />。

==鉴别==
如果誤食可能造成嚴重的症狀，包括死亡<ref name="Barbee et al">{{cite journal |author=Barbee G, Berry-Cabán C, Barry J, Borys D, Ward J, Salyer S |title=Analysis of mushroom exposures in Texas requiring hospitalization, 2005-2006 |journal=Journal of Medical Toxicology |volume=5 |issue=2 |pages=59–62 |year=2009 |pmid=19415588 |url=http://jmt.pennpress.org/strands/jmt/toc.htm;jsessionid=ECC1ED5314DF17993B4B357234FB1F8D?issue=20090502 |doi=10.1007/BF03161087 }}{{dead link|date=2018年2月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>，因此，在食用任何蕈類之前，必須先辨認之，只有正確地辨認出蕈菇的種類後才能確保安全。有些分類的真菌，例如[[鵝膏菌屬|鵝膏菌屬]]，同時包含有劇毒的（如[[毒鵝膏|毒鵝膏]]）和可食用的（如[[橙蓋鵝膏菌|橙蓋鵝膏菌]]）物種，而且外觀非常類似，因此務需謹慎。有些一般情況下可食用的蕈類仍可能造成危險，原因包括在少數人身上會造成[[過敏|過敏]]、儲存不當會造成食物中毒、生長在汙染嚴重的地方而累積了毒素或是搭配特定食物一起吃而導致中毒。<ref name=kalac00/>

